Sean's Audio database

- Controls Sean's entire audio collection, and acts as a media player, information tool, database, and wishlist.

Beta 0.84 - May 16th 2020 | Optimized for screens of resolution 1366x768 | Designed for Mozilla Firefox 11.0 and up. Not tested on other web browsers.

| Languages |

| Computer languages: CSS 3.0, HTML 5.3, JavaScript 1.8, JQuery 1.10, PHP 7.3, Ruby 2.6, XML 1.1. |

| Human languages: Bulgarian [ISO: BG], English [ISO: EN], Russian [ISO: RU], Ukrainian [ISO: UK]. | English for main content only, some sections use content in other languages.

Do not leak this program. This program doesn't contain much sensitive information, but I don't want it publicly released yet. If you are to leak it, I won't be mad. Contact me @ and respond with your comments on the project. Feedback is appreciated. Please text only, I do not respond to phone calls.

Todays downloads are for Fortnite sounds. I hate Fortnite, I see it as an overrated cashgrab, since it is an unoriginal shooter game that charges thousands for content that doesn't help you beat the game. It is also highly overpriced, would you rather buy a better computer, or spend $1000.00 on a handful of skins for a game that could go offline one day, never to be seen again? (and has gone down before on purpose)

However, it is part of the archival policy, so it was downloaded.

I have learned of the termination of BrawlBRSMSTx, one of the biggest video game soundtrack channels. Almost every company was cool with the music being there, except Nintendo, Nintendo was the 1/10 dentist that wanted to kill the product, and succeeded (for now)

Nintendo has always hated their fans. It has been obvious. A company is nothing without its supporters, so I don't know why the fuck they thought ANY of this was a good idea. They take down all music channels, but they won't provide ways of getting old Nintendo game music

From now on, Nintendo related music is on high alert, and I am willing to give anyone a copy of any of my Nintendo music files that I have already downloaded upon request to keep the spreading strong. The music will always be there, likely in an alternate site, or a file sharing service, so I don't know why Nintendo thinks they are going to win

I have started to hate Nintendo upon discovery of these things a couple years ago, and now my hate is fully solid. Fuck Nintendo. They made a lot of my childhood, but now that I am aware of what is going on, I really hope their company dies. They had it coming.

I added in support for jQuery, so that I could get a popup about page to work (it currently has issues, like the dialog coming up first thing without clicking the button, and me not finding a way to make the button open the popup) along with a new section for pictures of special builds, and a fix to the folding wisblist issue I couldn't fix last night. I want it to be detailed, and apples icon has been a perfect placeholder. Development has been going really well, and I really enjoy working on this project.

About this file - documentation

As a wishlist

This is a wishlist for new music and sound effects that I plan to purchase/download to my computer and add to my music collection. It serves as a wishlist, archiving the links to the songs I want to get.

Indexing

Songs and sound effects are counted on a daily basis whenever music or sound effects are added to the list.

Music is counted without a decimal, for example, a single song at the beginning of a list would have a (1) at the end of its name.

If a playlist came after that which contained 40 songs, there would be a bubble counting up the items in the playlist, and the previous song count, meaning a (41) would be at the end

Sound effects are a different category. They start out at (1.1) if there is more than 1 sound effect in a day, it will follow by (1.2) if a collection of sound effects were added, and the collection had 93 sound effects, it would be followed by (1.95) and so on

Counters

There are several counters across this file. On each daily list, where I add new content, there is a sound effect counter, and a song counter, counting how many songs and sound effects I added to the list. There are counters for days I added in to the list, how many changes I made, and total song and sound effect counts

TXT document style

This text document is styled uniquely. It has some python syntax in it.

As of the November 17th 2019 build, it is being converted to HTML5.

New entries

A new entry starts with the name of the song or sound effect, followed by its daily index number. Under that, is the link to the audio. If it is in a playlist, a counter of how many items in the playlist will be under the link, if not, a file path will be shown.

The file path starts with 1 of 2 different syntax:

(Add to: Music/ - this is for adding in music

(Add to: SFX/ - this is for adding in sound effects

Afterwards, the desired file path will be shown after that, not including the file names. Older versions didn't have the Music/ and SFX/ headers, they just had the (Add to: example/example)

Wikimedia - Wiktionary - утка ("Duck" in Russian)

Noun

owl

something incorrectly chosen or assumed

situation where something is incorrectly chosen or assumed

someone who incorrectly chooses or assumes

https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c3/Ru-%D1%83%D1%82%D0%BA%D0%B0.ogg

Wikimedia - Wiktionary - идти ("Go" in Russian") 2x = уткауткаидти (hopefully grammatically correct)

Verb

идти́ • (idtí) impf (perfective пойти́) (concrete verbs)

to go

Идём в кинотеа́тр! ― Idjóm v kinoteátr! ― Let's go to the movie theater!

to walk

(of precipitation) to fall

Идёт дождь. ― Idjót doždʹ. ― It’s raining.

Идёт снег. ― Idjót sneg. ― It’s snowing.

Идёт град. ― Idjót grad. ― It’s hailing.

to function, to work

Э́ти часы́ не иду́т. ― Éti časý ne idút. ― This clock/watch doesn't work.

to suit, to become (of wearing clothes)

Э́тот костю́м ему́ идёт. ― Étot kostjúm jemú idjót. ― This suit suits him.

(used in expressions)

Вре́мя идёт бы́стро. ― Vrémja idjót býstro. ― Time flies.

Э́то ещё куда́ ни шло. ― Éto ješčó kudá ni šlo. ― That's still all right. (colloquial)

Их това́ры иду́т хорошо́. ― Ix továry idút xorošó. ― Their products are selling well.

О чём идёт речь?

O čóm idjót rečʹ?

What is being talked about? / What is it all about? / What is the topic? / What are you guys talking about?

Речь идёт о двух/трёх веща́х. ― Rečʹ idjót o dvux/trjóx veščáx. ― [insert subject] is/are talking about two/three things.

Всё идёт по пла́ну. ― Vsjó idjót po plánu. ― Everything is going as planned.

Во ско́лько идёт э́та переда́ча? ― Vo skólʹko idjót éta peredáča? ― What time is this (television) program on?

Э́то не идёт ни в како́е сравне́ние с че́м-либо/ке́м-либо.

Éto ne idjót ni v kakóje sravnénije s čém-libo/kém-libo.

It cannot be compared with something/someone.

идти́ на компроми́сс ― idtí na kompromíss ― to compromise, make a compromise

идти́ на усту́пки ― idtí na ustúpki ― to compromise, make concessions

идти́ на риск ― idtí na risk ― to run a risk, take a chance

идти́ на всё ― idtí na vsjó ― to be ready to do anything, go to any length

идти́ по пята́м ― idtí po pjatám ― to follow in someone's footsteps; to follow on the heels of

Usage notes

Идти and пойти́ (pojtí) are Russian concrete verbs. Their counterpart, ходи́ть (xodítʹ), is an abstract verb.

Prefixed derivatives of this verb are formed using the combining form -йти́ (-jtí).

https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%D0%B8%D0%B4%D1%82%D0%B8

https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e0/Ru-%D0%B8%D0%B4%D1%82%D0%B8.ogg

Guideline notes from February 8th 2020

========================================================================================================================================================================================================

Audio collection guidelines

Index

Section 1 - Download (almost) everuthing

Section 1 - Download (almost) everything

With the audio collection, the goal is to download every piece of music ever listened to by Sean (that can be found) and for sound effects, there are different guidelines.

Significant/comedic sound effects and easy to grab onez are downloaded, but things like peoples voices, custom animal noises (voices of personal pets, and friends pets) are not a priority.

Wikimedia - Wiktionary - утка ("Duck" in Russian)

Noun

owl

something incorrectly chosen or assumed

situation where something is incorrectly chosen or assumed

someone who incorrectly chooses or assumes

https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c3/Ru-%D1%83%D1%82%D0%BA%D0%B0.ogg

Wikimedia - Wiktionary - идти ("Go" in Russian") 2x = уткауткаидти (hopefully grammatically correct)

Verb

идти́ • (idtí) impf (perfective пойти́) (concrete verbs)

to go

Идём в кинотеа́тр! ― Idjóm v kinoteátr! ― Let's go to the movie theater!

to walk

(of precipitation) to fall

Идёт дождь. ― Idjót doždʹ. ― It’s raining.

Идёт снег. ― Idjót sneg. ― It’s snowing.

Идёт град. ― Idjót grad. ― It’s hailing.

to function, to work

Э́ти часы́ не иду́т. ― Éti časý ne idút. ― This clock/watch doesn't work.

to suit, to become (of wearing clothes)

Э́тот костю́м ему́ идёт. ― Étot kostjúm jemú idjót. ― This suit suits him.

(used in expressions)

Вре́мя идёт бы́стро. ― Vrémja idjót býstro. ― Time flies.

Э́то ещё куда́ ни шло. ― Éto ješčó kudá ni šlo. ― That's still all right. (colloquial)

Их това́ры иду́т хорошо́. ― Ix továry idút xorošó. ― Their products are selling well.

О чём идёт речь?

O čóm idjót rečʹ?

What is being talked about? / What is it all about? / What is the topic? / What are you guys talking about?

Речь идёт о двух/трёх веща́х. ― Rečʹ idjót o dvux/trjóx veščáx. ― [insert subject] is/are talking about two/three things.

Всё идёт по пла́ну. ― Vsjó idjót po plánu. ― Everything is going as planned.

Во ско́лько идёт э́та переда́ча? ― Vo skólʹko idjót éta peredáča? ― What time is this (television) program on?

Э́то не идёт ни в како́е сравне́ние с че́м-либо/ке́м-либо.

Éto ne idjót ni v kakóje sravnénije s čém-libo/kém-libo.

It cannot be compared with something/someone.

идти́ на компроми́сс ― idtí na kompromíss ― to compromise, make a compromise

идти́ на усту́пки ― idtí na ustúpki ― to compromise, make concessions

идти́ на риск ― idtí na risk ― to run a risk, take a chance

идти́ на всё ― idtí na vsjó ― to be ready to do anything, go to any length

идти́ по пята́м ― idtí po pjatám ― to follow in someone's footsteps; to follow on the heels of

Usage notes

Идти and пойти́ (pojtí) are Russian concrete verbs. Their counterpart, ходи́ть (xodítʹ), is an abstract verb.

Prefixed derivatives of this verb are formed using the combining form -йти́ (-jtí).

https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%D0%B8%D0%B4%D1%82%D0%B8

https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e0/Ru-%D0%B8%D0%B4%D1%82%D0%B8.ogg

Future plans:

1. A massive file dedicated to all audio info, including all variations of this list

2. A working Firefox extension that lets me download videos directly

Update: I now have a working downloader, and I started downloading again on 8.17.2019. Unfortunately, it has 3 issues:

* Some content is watermarked upon download with a QR code

* Some MP4 downloads with the agent contain only the audio

* Downloads are very slow with the agent, a 1.9 megabyte file can take over 5 minutes to download

* When downloading with the agent, CPU usage goes extremely high, jumping from 29% to a range between 70% and 100%

The downloader stopped working for a few months, but as of late April/Early May 2020, I have been having some luck with it. There is a bug I am exploiting (I hope it isn't identified as a bug, so that it doesn't get patched) but here is the plan:

There is always a separate non-ADP option on ADP downloads. It has no CPU or QR code issues. I download this version first. It is in full resolution, but it doesn’t have any sound. I then do the CPU intensive one (the ADP one) which has the audio and the QR code. My future plan for when I get to it is to extract the audio from the ADP QR code version, and put it onto the soundless version to have the full resolution video with sound.

Some cons still exist, such as this option not being able to work for MKV videos, and the fact that I can't download any videos that are uploaded as MKV files, as the Matroska modules are missing or corrupted. The CPU mining is still a big issue too, but I have been making progress.

Download plan:

Vulnerable videos first:

Since YouTube has been overrun by malicious companies such as UMG, Nintendo (mainly takedowns from Nintendo, since they hate their fanbase), and more, videos can be taken down at any time.

To prevent data loss, I will go for vulnerable videos first. Vulnerable videos can:

* Have a low view count

* Be Nintendo related

* Remixes

* Videos that fall under fair use, but companies can abuse it

Videos that aren't considered vulnerable, are:

* Videos sponsored by Vevo

* Parody videos that are at least 10 years old (2010 or older)

* Videos by the official company

I will try to get the most vulnerable videos first. After that, I will go for the non-vulnerable content.

Media player info

First media player

Originally, I used VLC Media Player to play all my media. Occasionally, I would have to use Windows Media Player to play MID files because VLC couldn't handle them.

Due to the instability of my somewhat functional laptop from 2019, VLC constantly crashes itself, and possibly even the host laptop. So I have used Firefox's built in MP4, OGG, MP3, and WEBM player for content.

As of November 18th 2019, I still use Firefox for playing media

As of April 2nd 2020, I have switched back to VLC media player. I really missed it, and I can now have a lot more control over my music again. I love to change the pitch and the other effects. Plus, I can play files not playable in Firefox (such as MKV files)

Special folders

Starting on May 6th 2020, special folders were added to the music collection. These folders are above the !series folders, and are of importance level 4 (out of 6) they have different categories, and serve unique purposes.

The first special folder: !!HardSongsToFind was added on May 6th 2020. It contains all the songs that I hardly ever come across, or have difficulty finding a name for. The first file added to this was the Curb your Enthusiasm theme, as I constantly forgot its name.

On May 7th 2020, specific file type special folders were added, but currently remain dormant. They are planned to contain links to files of specific types, so that the experience can be even more custom. If you were to feel like playing a MID file, you can browse MIDI files, if you wanted to listen to an MP3, you can search for MP3 files, and so on.

Special folders contain a star icon. The name "special folder" was inspired by the Microsoft Windows counterpart with the same name (Common Windows special folders include the recycle bin, the 'my computer'/'this PC' folder, and more.

List of special folders

File type

In alphabetical order

!!AIFF (contains .aiff files) - Audio Interchange File Format (audio file)

!!FLAC (contains .flac files) - Free Lossless Audio Codec (audio file)

!!MIDI (contains .mid files) - musical instrument digital interface (audio file)

!!MKV (contains .mkv files) - Matroska multimedia container video (video file)

!!MP3 (contains .mp3 files) - MPEG 1 Audio Layer III (audio file)

!!MP4 (contains .mp4 files) - MPEG Part 14 (video file)

!!OGG (contains .ogg files) - OGG Vorbis (audio file)

!!WAV (contains .wav files) - Waveform audio file format (audio file)

!!WEBM (contains .webm files) - WEBM (video file)

!!WMV (contains .wmv files) - Windows Media Video (video file)

Search help

In alphabetical order

!!Hard to find songs (contains songs that are rarely come across, or hard to find)

Icons

The audio collection has a set of icons for different situations. Icons help separate the level of completeness of each playlist or single.

Windows icons (Windows 8, 8.1, 10)

This icon is for folders that are nonexistent (for when I marked a playlist for a song that doesn't exist)

This icon is for folders that have some of the needed files, but not all of them.

This icon is for folders that don't have any files yet.

This icon is for folders that are complete.

This icon is for section tags that help users navigate through the library with the keyboard.

This icon is for family and friend funeral music.

This icon is for series, or playlists of playlists.

This icon is for special folders.

This icon is for Wii channel compilations.

This icon is for MP4 and other video files within a playlist.

This icon is for MP3 and other audio files within a playlist.

This icon is for Archive folders (folders with archived audio that likely won't be heard often, and is separate)

This icon is for new root folders outside the root folder (in the oldest system, each root would have 100 folders, then you would need to progress further)

Playlist files

VLC playlists (Windows)

On April 2nd 2020, Sean started using VLC media player again as an experiment. The experiment went very well, and VLC was kept as the main media player again, and Sean was unbelievably happy to be using VLC again.

One new task that is now done is the creation of VLC playlists after each work session. There are usually 3 playlists created each day.

The first playlist of the day (starting April 4th 2020) is the afternoon journaling playlist. This may fall in the morning on some days, but this is just its name. It refers to the first work session on the day where I have access to VLC and my music collection.

The second playlist of the day (starting April 4th 2020) is the afternoon website work playlist. This may fall in the morning and afternoon on some days, but this is just its name. It refers to the second work session of the day where I have access to VLC and my music collection. It typically comes straight after doing daily khan academy lectures on my main khan academy account.

The third playlist of the day (starting April 4th 2020) is the nighttime website work playlist. This refers to the third work session of the day, and can also span for journaling, music collection work, and other projects right before the final shutdown of the day. This is the last playlist of the day.

The first playlist is called Resurgence, as it is the first playlist after using VLC again. The 2nd and 3rd playlists are not labeled, but are the test run of VLC on my computer. Starting with the 4th playlist and onward, the 3 playlist a day system is used. VLC has not had any problems for a whole month, so I am really glad I took the risk.
